>`, and retain with `(source_key.clone(), record.source_record_hash.clone())`.\\n\\n2. [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:66](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:66) `updated-at` is written before any transcript rows are pushed. If a later `list_push` fails, GitMeta can show a refreshed session/source even though the batch only partially landed. The data-flow reads as “metadata update completed” before the actual append side effect.  \\nPOC fix: compute `updated_at` before the writes if desired, but call `handle.set(...:updated-at...)` after the record loop succeeds.\\n\\n3. [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:53](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:53) `retain` clones every incoming `source_record_hash`, including records that are immediately discarded as existing duplicates. For growing transcripts this repeats allocation on the full historical prefix every capture.  \\nPOC fix: make the branch explicit so only new records clone into the dedupe set:\\n```rust\\nrecords.retain(|record| {\\n    if transcript_hashes.contains(&record.source_record_hash) {\\n        false\\n    } else {\\n        transcript_hashes.insert(record.source_record_hash.clone());\\n        true\\n    }\\n});\\n```\\nThat trades one extra lookup on new rows for avoiding allocation on all old rows.\\n\\n4. [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:78](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:78) `source_key` is cloned into a fresh `String` for every transcript row solely to serialize JSON. This is small, but it is repeated per record and the caller already owns a stable `String` for the whole batch.  \\nPOC fix: make `TranscriptRecord` borrow the source key:\\n```rust\\nstruct TranscriptRecord<'a> {\\n    source_key: &'a str,\\n    ...\\n}\\n```\\nThen `from_parsed` can assign `source_key` directly and remove the per-row allocation.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>"}]}}}